M2X update 1.7.12 is up in the [usual](http://spacedock.info/mod/473/Mk2%20Stockalike%20Expansion) [places](https://github.com/SuicidalInsanity/Mk2Expansion/releases/tag/1.7.0.1), which mainly fixes various RPM/ASET IVA config issues

@Grenartia: Some of the problem you describe stems from making a compromise between visibility and instrumentation space - I wanted IVAs you could see the runway from, which meant moving instrument panels down or going for smaller displays to get them to fit; in some cases this does require tilting the camera down a little to see the displays. Given the limited instrument space available, though, I can't really make the displays any bigger unless I remodel the IVAs, which would be a time consuming endeavor I don't have time for. Not sure what to say about the fishhead cockpit, since it doesn't have an RPM IVA config, but the current IVA setup means that I probably will need to rework/remodel it at some point.

